tv-half-year-revenues-2023-1235681170%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ftv%2Fglobal%2Fitv-half-year-revenues-2023-1235681170%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Gyanvapi%20Mosque%20Committee's%20Plea%20Against%20Maintainability%20of%20Suit%20Not%20Dismissed%2C%20Clarifies%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2026%2C%20rectified%20an%20inadvertent%20error%20by%20which%20it%20had%20on%20Monday%2C%20July%2024%2C%20disposed%20of%20a%20plea%20on%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20related%20to%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20and%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20temple%20at%20Varanasi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fasis-scientific-survey-begins-at-gyanvapi-mosque-amidst-heavy-security%5C%22%3Ehalted%20the%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20mosque%20until%205%20pm%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20July%2026%2C%20ordered%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court.%20The%20survey%20by%20the%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India%20(ASI)%20was%20ordered%20to%20ascertain%20whether%20the%20mosque%20was%20built%20over%20a%20pre-existing%20Hindu%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20error%20was%20pointed%20out%20by%20Huzefa%20Ahmadi%2C%20representing%20the%20Committee%20of%20Management%20Anjuman%20Intezamia%20of%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%2C%20that%20the%20court%20had%20inadvertently%20disposed%20of%20the%20main%20plea%20instead%20of%20the%20interlocutory%20application%2C%20which%20only%20sought%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20ASI%20survey.%20The%20main%20plea%20referred%20to%20a%20special%20leave%20petition%20filed%20by%20the%20Committee%20challenging%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20dismissal%20of%20its%20Order%207%20Rule%2011%20CPC%20(Code%20of%20Civil%20Procedure)%20plea%20against%20the%20maintainability%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Worshippers%E2%80%99%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-clarifies-order-in-gyanvapi-case-says-mosque-committees-petition-challenging-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-233643%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%20%3Cem%3ELivelaw%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Ahmadi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20correction%20needed%20in%20the%20Monday%20order.%20Your%20Lordships%20accidentally%20disposed%20the%20SLP.%20We%20had%20moved%20for%20the%20IA%20%5Binterlocutory%20application%5D.%20The%20only%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20matter%20is%20going%20on%20before%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20on%20a%20day-to-day%20basis.%20The%20SLP%20(special%20leave%20petition)%20is%20against%20an%20Order%207%20Rule%2011%20issue%E2%80%A6that%20has%20been%20disposed%20of%20but%20we%20never%20argued%20on%20that.%20We%20only%20argued%20on%20the%20ASI%20survey%20point.%20Now%20before%20the%20Allahabad%20HC%2C%20it%20can%20be%20argued%20that%20our%20appeal%20has%20been%20dismissed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20hearing%20Ahmadi%E2%80%99s%20explanation%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20promptly%20corrected%20the%20order%2C%20clarifying%20that%20what%20was%20disposed%20of%20was%20the%20interlocutory%20petition%20and%20not%20the%20special%20leave%20petition%20as%20assumed%20earlier.%20He%20then%20ordered%20the%20court%20staff%20to%20delete%20Paragraph%2010%20of%20the%20order%2C%20which%20led%20to%20confusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202022%2C%20the%20Masjid%20Committee%20had%20moved%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20challenging%20the%20maintainability%20of%20a%20suit%20filed%20by%20five%20Hindu%20women%2C%20who%20sought%20the%20right%20to%20worship%20inside%20the%20Gyanvapi%20mosque%20compound.%20The%20plea%20was%20filed%20under%C2%A0Order%207%20Rule%2011%20CPC.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Masjid%20Committee%20had%20to%20move%20the%20high%20court%20because%20the%20same%20plea%20was%20turned%20down%20by%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court.%20The%20district%20court%20held%20that%20the%20Hindu%20petitioners%20cannot%20be%20barred%20from%20worshipping%20rights%20under%20the%20Places%20of%20Worship%20(Special%20Provisions)%20Act%2C%201991%2C%20The%20Waqf%20Act%201995%2C%20and%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Shri%20Kashi%20Vishwanath%20Temple%20Act%2C%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20then%20dismissed%20Masjid%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20petition%2C%20upholding%20the%20Varanasi%20district%20court%E2%80%99s%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Hindu%20petitioners%20filed%20an%20application%20before%20a%20trial%20court%20requesting%20a%20survey%20of%20the%20mosque%20by%20the%20ASI%2C%20which%20was%20allowed%20on%20July%2021.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20then%20stayed%20the%20trial%20court%20order%2C%20stating%20that%20the%20survey%20will%20be%20on%20hold%20until%205%20pm%20on%20July%2026%20to%20allow%20the%20Masjid%20committee%20to%20challenge%20the%20survey%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1690437910000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F15184329%2F20230103_124657.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-committees-plea-against-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-clarifies-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20in%20its%20previous%20order%20had%20inadvertently%20disposed%20of%20the%20main%20plea%20instead%20of%20the%20interlocutory%20application%2C%20which%20only%20sought%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20survey%20by%20Archaeological%20Survey%20of%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgyanvapi-mosque-committees-plea-against-maintainability-of-suit-not-dismissed-clarifies-sc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Arjun%20Tendulkar%20Sets%20Internet%20On%20Fire%20With%20His%20Latest%20Six-Pack%20Abs%20Pic%22%