s%20the%20debate%20remained%20inconclusive%20and%20there%20was%20no%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThrice%20governments%20have%20fallen%20during%20the%20vote%20of%20confidence%20-%20the%20VP%20Singh%20government%20in%201990%2C%20H%20D%20Devegowda%20government%20in%201997%20and%20the%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20government%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%207%2C%201990%2C%20VP%20Singh%20moved%20a%20Motion%20of%20Confidence%20in%20the%20Council%20of%20Ministers.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated%20after%20the%20BJP%20withdrew%20its%20support%20over%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20issue.%20He%20lost%20the%20motion%20by%20142%20votes%20to%20346%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%201997%2C%20the%20H%20D%20Devegowda%20government%20lost%20a%20vote%20of%20confidence%20on%20April%2011.%20Devegowda's%2010-month-old%20coalition%20government%20fell%20as%20292%20MPs%20voted%20against%20the%20government%2C%20while%20158%20MPs%20supported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20coming%20to%20power%20in%201998%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20had%20moved%20a%20confidence%20motion%2C%20which%20he%20lost%20by%20one%20vote%20on%20April%2017%2C%201999%20due%20to%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20list%20of%20no%20confidence%20motions%20moved%20previously%3A%201.%20August%201963%20-%20The%20first%20ever%20no%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20in%20the%20third%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20August%201963%20against%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20by%20Congress%20leader%20Acharya%20Kripalani.%20This%20was%20immediately%20after%20losing%20to%20China%20in%20the%201962%20war.%20The%20debate%20went%20on%20for%20four%20days%2C%20for%20over%2020%20hours.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20motion%20was%20defeated%2C%20with%20only%2062%20MPs%20supporting%20it%20and%20347%20opposing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E2.%20September%201964%20-%20A%20no%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20by%20NC%20Chatterjee%20against%20the%20government%20of%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri.%20Voting%20took%20place%20on%20September%2018%2C%201964%2C%20and%20307%20MPs%20voted%20against%20the%20motion%20while%2050%20voted%20for%20it.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E3.%20March%201965%20-%20The%20motion%20was%20moved%20by%20Kendrapara%20MP%20S%20N%20Dwivedy%20against%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20government.%20Debate%20took%20place%20on%20March%2016%2C%201965%2C%20and%20the%20motion%20was%20defeated%20with%20only%2044%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20while%20315%20voted%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E4.%20August%201965%20-%20A%20no%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20by%20erstwhile%20Swatantra%20Party%20MP%20MR%20Masani.%20Voting%20took%20place%20on%20August%2026%2C%201965%2C%20and%20was%20negated%20with%20only%2066%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20while%20318%20MPs%20opposed%20the%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E5.%20August%201966-%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20at%20the%20time%20took%20over%20as%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20in%20January%201966.%20A%20no%20confidence%20motion%20against%20her%20government%20was%20moved%20by%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20MP%20Hirendranath%20Mukherjee.%20The%20motion%20was%20supported%20by%2061%20MPs%2C%20while%20270%20MPs%20opposed%20it%20and%20the%20motion%20was%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E6.%20November%201966%20-%20Indira%20Gandhi's%20government%20faced%20a%20second%20no%20confidence%20motion%20in%20a%20year%2C%20which%20was%20moved%20by%20UM%20Trivedi%2C%20noted%20lawyer%20and%20politician%20of%20Bharatiya%20Jan%20Sangh.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated%20with%2036%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20and%20235%20MPs%20voting%20against%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E7.%20March%201976%20-%20In%20the%20fourth%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Atal%20Bihari%20Vajpayee%20had%20moved%20a%20no%20confidence%20motion%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government.%20The%20trust%20vote%20took%20place%20on%20March%2020%2C%201967%2C%20and%20162%20MPs%20voted%20against%20the%20government%2C%20while%20257%20voted%20in%20support.%20This%20was%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20votes%20polled%20in%20support%20of%20a%20no%20confidence%20motion%20against%20the%20government%20till%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E8.%20November%201967%20-%20A%20no%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20by%20Madhu%20Limaye%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government.%20Voting%20took%20place%20on%20November%2024%2C%201967%2C%20and%20was%20defeated%20with%2088%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20and%20215%20MPs%20opposing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E9.%20February%201968%20-%20No%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20by%20Balraj%20Madhok%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government.%20Voting%20took%20place%20on%20February%2028%2C%201968%2C%20and%20was%20defeated%20with%2075%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20and%20215%20MPs%20opposing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E10.%20November%201968%20-%20No%20confidence%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20by%20Bharatiya%20Jana%20Sangh's%20Kanwar%20Lal%20Gupta.%20Voting%20took%20place%20on%20November%2013%2C%201968%2C%20and%20was%20defeated%20with%2090%20MPs%20supporting%20it%2C%20and%20222%20opposing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E11.%20February%201969%20-%20A%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20government%20led%20by%20Indira%20Gandhi%20by%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Marxist)%20leader%20P%20Ramamurti.%20The%20motion%20was%20supported%20by%2086%20MPs%2C%20and%20opposed%20by%20215%20MPs.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E12.%20July%201970%20-%20A%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20by%20Madhu%20Limaye.%20The%20motion%20got%20support%20of%20137%20MPs%2C%20and%20opposed%20by%20243%20MPs.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E13.%20November%201973%20-%20A%20motion%20was%20moved%20against%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20government%20by%20CPI-M%20MP%20Jyotirmoy%20Basu.%20The%20motion%20was%20defeated%2C%20with%20251%20MPs%20opposing%20it%