egal%20Crossroads%3A%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Previous%20judgments%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202021%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Common%20Cause%E2%80%99s%20case%20had%20ordered%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9CAny%20extension%20of%20tenure%20granted%20to%20persons%20holding%20the%20post%20of%20Director%20of%20Enforcement%20after%20attaining%20the%20age%20of%20superannuation%20should%20be%20for%20a%20short%20period.%20We%20do%20not%20intend%20to%20interfere%20with%20the%20extension%20of%20tenure%20of%20the%20second%20Respondent%20(Mishra)%20in%20the%20instant%20case%20for%20the%20reason%20that%20his%20tenure%20is%20coming%20to%20an%20end%20in%20November%202021.%20We%20make%20it%20clear%20that%20no%20further%20extension%20shall%20be%20granted%20to%20the%20second%20Respondent.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20get%20over%20the%202021%20judgement%2C%20the%20government%20amended%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%20Act%2C%20the%20Delhi%20Special%20Police%20Establishment%20Act%2C%20and%20the%20Fundamental%20Rules%2C%20to%20provide%20for%20yearly%20extensions%20of%20the%20tenures%20of%20the%20CBI%20director%20and%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20for%20a%20period%20of%20up%20to%20five%20years.%20These%20amendments%20were%20also%20challenged%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20a%20second%20challenge%20by%20Jaya%20Thakur%20and%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-enforcement-directorate-sk-mishra-extensions-illegal%5C%22%3Eamendments%20were%20upheld%20this%20year%20in%202023%2C%20but%20not%20the%20extension%3C%2Fa%3E%20granted%20to%20Mishra.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20ruled%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20clear%20that%20this%20court%20issued%20a%20specific%20mandamus%20that%20no%20further%20extension%20shall%20be%20granted%20to%20the%20second%20respondent.%20undisputedly%2C%20the%20union%20of%20India%20as%20well%20as%20the%20respondent%20no.2-%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20Mishra%20in%20writ%20petition%20(civil)%20no.%20456%20of%202022%20herein%20were%20parties%20to%20the%20said%20proceedings%E2%80%A6.%20this%20court%20has%20specifically%20issued%20a%20mandamus%20that%20no%20further%20extension%20shall%20be%20granted%20to%20the%20second%20respondent.%20the%20union%20of%20India%20and%20respondent%20no.%202%20were%20both%20parties%20in%20the%20proceedings%20before%20this%20court%20in%20writ%20petition%20(civil)%20no.%201374%20of%202020%20%5BCommon%20Cause%20(2021)%5D.%20The%20mandamus%20issued%20to%20the%20parties%20was%20binding%20on%20them.%20we%2C%20therefore%2C%20find%20that%20respondent%20no.1%20could%20not%20have%20issued%20orders%20dated%2017th%20November%202021%20and%2017th%20November%202022%20in%20breach%20of%20the%20mandamus%20issued%20by%20this%20court%20vide%20its%20judgment%20dated%208th%20September%202021%20in%20common%20cause%20(2021).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20however%20allowed%20Mishra%20to%20continue%20till%20the%20end%20of%20July%202023.%20This%20decision%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenforcement-directorate-sanjay-mishra-supreme-court-fatf%5C%22%3Einfluenced%20by%20considerations%20of%20the%20terror-financing%20watchdog%20FATF%E2%80%99s%20review%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20time%20needed%20to%20appoint%20the%20new%20director%20of%20enforcement.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20said%3A%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20inclined%20to%20take%20into%20consideration%20the%20concern%20expressed%20by%20the%20union%20of%20India%20with%20regard%20to%20FATF%20review.%20we%20are%20further%20inclined%20to%20take%20into%20consideration%20that%20the%20process%20of%20appointing%20the%20director%20of%20enforcement%20is%20likely%20to%20take%20some%20time.%20In%20that%20view%20of%20the%20matter%2C%20we%20find%20that%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20the%20transition%20to%20be%20smooth%20in%20the%20larger%20public%20interest%2C%20it%20will%20be%20appropriate%20to%20permit%20respondent%20no.2%20to%20continue%20to%20be%20in%20office%20till%2031%20July%202023.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20face%20of%20the%20judgement%20and%20nearing%20the%20second%20mandamus%20to%20quit%2C%20the%20government%20has%20now%20sought%20an%20%E2%80%9Cextension%20of%20the%20date%20upto%2015.10.2023%20which%20the%20Respondent%20No.%202%20may%E2%80%A6be%20permitted%20to%20continue%20in%20office%2C%20in%20view%20of%20the%20ongoing%20FATF%20Review%20which%20is%20at%20a%20critical%20stage%20where%20submissions%20on%20effectiveness%20have%20been%20made%20on%2021.07.2023%20and%20on-site%20visit%20is%20scheduled%20to%20be%20conducted%20in%20November%2C%202023.%20At%20such%20critical%20juncture%2C%20it%20is%20essential%20to%20have%20an%20individual%20who%20is%20well-acquainted%20with%20the%20overall%20status%20of%20money%20laundering%20investigations%20and%20proceedings%20across%20the%20country%20and%20also%20the%20intricacies%20of%20the%20procedures%2C%20operations%20and%20activities%20of%20the%20investigating%20agency%2C%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20affairs%20at%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Enforcement.%20This%20is%20necessary%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20assessment%20team%20can%20be%20promptly%20and%20ably%20assisted%20with%20necessary%20reports%2C%20information%2C%20statistics%20etc.%20Any%20transition%20in%20leadership%20at%20the%20Directorate%20of%20Enforcement%20at%20this%20stage%2C%20would%20significantly%20impair%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20agency%20to%20provide%20necessary%20assistance%20to%20and%20co-operation%20with%20the%20assessment%20team%20and%20thereby%20adversely%20impact%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20interests.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsk-mishra-enforcement-directorate-fatf-evaluation%5C%22%3EAt%20SC%2C%20Modi%20Govt%20Justified%20S.K.%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20Extension%20Citing%20FATF%20Review.%20How%20Key%20Is%20His%20Role%20in%20it%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98In%20the%20name%20of%20God%2C%20go%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20ill-behoves%20a%20government%20to%20act%20like%20a%20recalcitrant%20debtor%2C%20seeking%20a%20further%20lease%20of%20time.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20is%20no%20constitutional%20or%20statutory%20body%20but%20a%20mere%20department%20of%20the%20finance%20ministry.%20Its%20director%20can%20easily%20be%20substituted%20by%20an%20official%20to%20act%20upon%20the%20incumbent%E2%80%99s%20departure.%20The%20incumbent%20himself%20is%20not%20barred%20from%20offering%20his%20expertise%20as%20a%20consultant%20or%20otherwise%20to%20the%20government%2C%20even%20for%20purposes%20like%20the%20FATF%20review.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20second%20judgement%20in%20%3Cem%3EJaya%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EThakur%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20is%20based%20on%20its%20earlier%20judgement%20in%20%3Cem%3ECommon%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ECause%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20had%20specifically%20ruled%20out%20an%20extension%20to%20S.K.%20Mishra%20in%20particular.%20The%20court%20has%20had%20to%20repeat%20itself%20twice%2C%20to%20rule%20that%20no%20further%20extensions%20can%20be%20given.%20A%20third%20extension%20will%20simply%20undermine%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20court%20and%20the%20efficacy%20of%20its%20mandamus.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20judgments%20of%20the%20court%20cannot%20be%20treated%20as%20having%20been%20writ%20in%20water.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20court%20and%20the%20government%20may%20do%20well%20to%20recollect%20Oliver%20Cromwell%E2%80%99s%20admonition%20and%20say%