%3Cp%3EThe%20film%20highlights%20the%20arc%20of%20emotions%20that%20Lakshmi%20(a%20Dalit%20woman%20living%20in%20rural%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20essayed%20by%20Shabana%20Azmi)%20goes%20through%20as%20she%20begins%20working%20for%20an%20upper-caste%20%3Cem%3Ezamindar%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20son%20Surya%2C%20who%20does%20not%20delve%20too%20much%20into%20the%20caste%20difference.%20The%20movie%20brings%20to%20the%20front%20issues%20of%20patriarchy%2C%20caste%2C%20class%20and%20gender%20in%20a%20tale%20that%20is%20both%20beautiful%20and%20sad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20decades%2C%20Indian%20cinema%20has%20touched%20upon%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F16955%2Fmen-silently-building-caste-less-india-one-child-time%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epervasive%20caste%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20India%20through%20many%20films%20%E2%80%94%20some%20deemed%20controversial%20yet%20milestones%2C%20like%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Bandit%20Queen%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Esome%20that%20resonated%20with%20wider%20audiences%20like%20%3Cem%3EArticle%2015%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EJai%20Bhim%3C%2Fem%3E%3B%20and%20some%20that%20used%20humour%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20gravity%20of%20caste%20discrimination%2C%20like%20%3Cem%3EChameli%20ki%20Shaadi%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201080px)%20100vw%2C%201080px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FKahi-Debe-Sandesh-1689943464.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20still%20from%20Kahi%20Debe%20Sandesh%20(1965)%20directed%20by%20Manu%20Nayak%2C%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FKahi-Debe-Sandesh-1689943464.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FKahi-Debe-Sandesh-1689943464-300x300.jpg%2030